# Coding discipline (L0 floor)

Always-on floor for product/package code. Full rule table + patterns: [afenda-coding-discipline](../skills/afenda-coding-discipline/SKILL.md) (load after the product farm is fixed). This rule does **not** own API SSOT, UI compose, or review process.

## Binding floor

| Topic | Rule |
|-------|------|
| External data | `unknown` → validate (Zod / owning schema); no product-path `any` without a change-note justification |
| Casts | No unearned `as`; prefer `satisfies`; brand only after parse |
| Variants | Discriminated unions (`kind` / `type` / `ok`); exhaust `never` in defaults |
| Brands | Prefer [API-003](../../docs/api/API-003-api-types.md) brands at boundaries — do not invent parallel brand shapes |
| API outcomes | `ActionResult<T>` (`ok: true \| false`) — not tutorial `{ success, data }` envelopes |
| UI imports | `import { … } from "@afenda/ui-system"` only — no barrel bypass |
| Env | `import { env } from "@afenda/env"` — no raw `process.env` for product config |
| Lint | Biome + `@afenda/config` — do not invent ESLint/Prettier stacks |
| Layout | Greenfield under `apps/web/**` and `packages/*` only |
| Correctness | No silent “shouldn’t happen” branches; delete dead code; comments = WHY only |

## PREFLIGHT

When this turn edits product/package code or applies this floor, list **`coding-discipline`** under **Rules**. List **`afenda-coding-discipline`** under **Skills** only if that skill was loaded this turn.

## Deeper work

Typed refactor / brands / unions / boundary hygiene beyond this floor → load [afenda-coding-discipline](../skills/afenda-coding-discipline/SKILL.md) + [reference.md](../skills/afenda-coding-discipline/reference.md). Route-outs (API SSOT, review, simplify, React perf) stay in that skill.
